PPSA Installer Live Image
=========================

This is a Debian Live ISO that lets you install PPSA onto a spare
disk or partition on your machine. It is meant to be written to a
USB drive (with Rufus or `dd`) and booted via the firmware boot
menu (typically F12 on desktops, F2/F8/F10 on laptops).

After boot, the installer TUI appears on tty1.

Usage
-----

1. Write the ISO to a USB:
   - Rufus (Windows):  select the ISO, click Start
   - dd (Linux):       sudo dd if=ppsa-installer-vX.Y.Z.iso of=/dev/sdX bs=4M status=progress

2. Boot the machine from the USB (F12 / boot menu).

3. The installer shows candidate drives and partitions. Pick one.

4. The installer writes PPSA to the selected target.

5. Reboot, F12 into the disk that now holds PPSA. Done.

Contents
--------

- /usr/local/bin/ppsa-install        The TUI installer
- /etc/systemd/system/ppsa-installer.service  Autostart on tty1
- /lib/live/mount/medium/ppsa/        Bundled PPSA image (read at install time)
- /var/log/ppsa-installer.log        Installer log (preserved on the live USB)

Re-running the installer
------------------------

After install, drop to a shell (Enter at the completion banner) and run:

    sudo ppsa-install

or simply reboot the live USB to launch it again.

See docs/dual-boot-install.md in the PPSA repository for the full guide.
